        <updateDate>2015-09-04T15:00:49Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Veterans Dignified Burial Act </strong></p> <p>Directs the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA): (1) upon confirming the veteran status of a deceased veteran in the custody of a local medical examiner, funeral director, county service group, or other similar entity, to request from that entity the specific date of the veteran's scheduled interment; and (2) during each 30-day period following the request to repeat it until the entity confirms the scheduled internment date or that the veteran has been interred.</p> <p>Requires the VA, by March 1 of each year, to report to the House and Senate Veterans' Affairs Committees on unclaimed deceased veterans interred after the 30-day period following the initial VA request.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
